  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka Treasuries yields down",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka has sold 55 billion rupees of Treasury bills with yields down across maturities and most of the money taken from 3-month bills, data from the state debt office showed.",
        "The debt office sold 45 billion rupees of 3-month bills at 31.5 percent down 61 basis points after offering 25 billion rupees.",
        "The cut-off for the 3-month bill is estimated at a little over 31.40 percent.",
        "230 million rupees of 6-month bills were sold at 29.97 percent, down 104 basis points, after offering 15 billion rupees.",
        "9.4 billion rupees of 12-month bills were sold at 29.82 percent, down 5 basis points after offering 15 billion rupees.",
        "The debt office offered 55 billion rupees of bills and sold them all. (Colombo/July 20/2022)"
      ],
